Carol Mayo Jenkins https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carol_Mayo_Jenkins 0 Carol Mayo Jenkins (born November 24, 1938) is an American actress who is most famous for playing Elizabeth Sherwood, a liberal and stern but fair-minded English teacher at New York City's High School for the Performing Arts on the T.V. series Fame. She left the show at the end of its fifth season in 1986 but made a return for the series finale a year later. She also appeared in the television shows Models Inc., Matlock, and Max Headroom. She teaches acting at the University of Tennessee, where she appears frequently on the Clarence Brown Theatre stage.
